c graph-d-separation-v0 chain-conditioned-blocks
c Variables:
c 1 = the skeleton path a-b-c exists and is selected.
c 2 = b is the middle non-collider on that path in a -> b -> c.
c 3 = b is in the conditioning set.
c 4 = the path is active, matching the rejected d-connected claim.
c The last clause encodes the d-separation rule: a conditioned non-collider
c blocks an otherwise selected path.
